Download logo World Health Organization (WHO) procures COVID-19 diagnostic testing equipment to improve lab capacity in Lagos State, the epicentre of the pandemic in Nigeria. Through DFID support, Lagos State labs are now able test up to 2,000 samples daily. Distributed by APO Group on behalf of WHO Regional Office for Africa.